news.title: Ajmera Realty posts net profit of Rs 34.18 crore in Q2 FY23
news.para: The company's net consolidated income stood at Rs 187.14 crore in Q2 FY23, a growth of 86.99 per cent from Rs 100.08 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Berger Paints posts net profit of Rs 219.51 crore in Q2 FY23
news.para: The company's net consolidated income stood at Rs 2,683.50 crore in Q2 FY23, a growth of 19.91 per cent from Rs 2,238 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Bengaluru: KSPCB fines Venkateshwara Builders for SWD buffer violation
news.para: The EC notice was issued as per the National Green Tribunal, Southern Zone, Chennai to Giri Babu GK and Mithun Gowda K of Venkateshwara Builders, Balaji Layout, Kaggadasapura in CV Raman Nagar.

news.title: Unauthorised construction bane to city's development: Delhi HC
news.para: The observation came while dismissing an appeal against an order of demolition of unauthorised construction carried out in a property in south Delhi's Hauz Khas.

news.title: Won't vacate homes without a compensation plan: Chintels Paradiso residents
news.para: An order by the district town planner to get two towers of Chintels Paradiso vacated at the earliest has left 42 families living there with an uncertain future.

news.title: Soon, MahaRERA valuers to check progress of projects
news.para: These valuers or inspectors would be certified by the income tax department or the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Board of India and carry out site visits.

news.title: Noida: Yamuna Buildtech, Hemisphere, others penalised for GRAP violation
news.para: "A penalty of Rs 5 lakh has been imposed on real estate developer Hemisphere over violation of norms at its project in Sector 27 while a penalty of Rs 50,000 was imposed on Yamuna Buildtech private limited after construction material was found kept in the open in its project in Sector 27," the Greater Noida Authority said.

news.title: UK house prices fall as rising mortgage rates temper property market
news.para: The Royal Institution of Chartered Surveyors (RICS) house price balance, which measures the difference between the percentage of surveyors reporting price rises and those seeing a fall, tumbled to -2 in October from +30 in September.

news.title: Godrej & Boyce terms land acquisition for bullet train project process as illegal
news.para: ​Godrej & Boyce Manufacturing also refuted allegations levelled against it by the state government and the NHSRCL that it was causing unnecessary hurdles and impediment in the land acquisition process and was hence delaying the project.

news.title: After 20 years, Jaipur development body frees own land worth Rs 300 crore from encroachers
news.para: The property was registered in the name of JDA in 1997, and the encroachers had taken possession of it around the same time. The encroachers constructed godowns, warehouses and offices on it.

news.title: WeWork to exit 40 locations in U.S. to cut costs
news.para: The closures are expected to cost about $200 million in remaining rent payments on the leases, while contributing roughly $140 million to annual adjusted core earnings, WeWork Chief Executive Sandeep Mathrani said.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh government can't allot house sites to poor in capital region, contend farmers
news.para: The high court held that the lands pooled for one purpose cannot be alienated for other purpose and the notified masterplan cannot be changed.

news.title: Chintels Paradiso tower residents allege lack of clarity over compensation
news.para: Despite this direction, Tower-D allottees said the district administration had muddled the situation. They alleged that the structural audit report on the basis of which the demolition was ordered was not even shared with them.

news.title: Peroorkada flyover construction to hit 95 land owners, 80 commercial firms: SIA report
news.para: As per the report, four houses will be completely demolished for the scheme while nine houses will be partially affected. The land acquisition will also impact 80 commercial buildings.

news.title: Over 600 Chandigarh housing board flats found locked in second survey
news.para: The CHB had decided to carry out a second survey of 1,268 flats allotted under the Rehabilitation Scheme, Small Flat Scheme and the Affordable Rental Housing Scheme which were found locked during the first survey done in July-September.
